Incontinentia pigmenti (Bloch-Sulzberger syndrome). A case report.
 Incontinentia pigmenti is a rare genodermatosis with multiple manifestations affecting the skeletal, ocular, dental, and other tissues.
 More than 95% of reported cases occur in females, and more than 60% of reported cases involve some dental abnormality.
 A brief review of the literature and a case in a 7-year-old girl with the disease are presented.
